what are the side effect of drinking coffee i drink at least cups of coffee a day i'm almost wut do coffee do to u study by researchers at duke university medical center shows that caffeine taken in the morning has effects on the body that persist until bedtime and amplifies stress consistently throughout the day the caffeine we drink enhances the effects of the stresses we experience so if we have a stressful job drinking coffee makes our body respond more to the ordinary stresses we experience he said the combination of stress and caffeine has a multiplying or synergistically negative effect quitting caffeine could be particularly beneficial for people suffering from high blood pressure just as diet and exercise can help keep blood pressure under control the researchers said that despite the perceived safety of overwhelmingly popular caffeinated beverages such as coffee the drug does show short term negative health effects that if continued over a period of years could increase risk of heart attack and stroke caffeine toxicity is known to cause excitement agitation restlessness shifting states of consciousness and toxic psychosis mimicking amphetamine psychosis allergic individuals may be erroneously diagnosed medicated and lost in a dark disturbed world until death it was also found that regular consumption of caffeinated coffee or tea or total caffeine intake was associated with an incidence of colorectal cancers drinking coffeee makes you jittery and unable to sleep Sleep Word of Wisdom Coffee Hypertension Psychosis Bipolar disorder Cannabis (drug) Cancer Stroke Yerba mate Insomnia Hypoglycemia Tobacco smoking Drug addiction Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Breastfeeding Chronic fatigue syndrome Urinary incontinence Clinical depression Milk Alcoholism Atkins Nutritional Approach Anxiety Tocopherol Methamphetamine Amphetamine Asthma Alzheimer's disease Folic acid Prostate cancer Fecal incontinence Narcolepsy Multiple sclerosis Diabetes mellitus Common co